 :tx/rationale "DESIGN: Session Working Set (SWS) — the missing temporal locality layer. Store is eternal (all datoms, all sessions). Agent attention is ephemeral (single context window). Between them: the session working set — the hot entities an agent is actively engaging. Three components: (1) SessionWorkingSet struct tracking active_tasks, session_entity, session_start_wall, recent_entities. (2) session_boost multiplier in R(t): 3.0x for in-progress, 2.0x for sibling tasks (same EPIC), 1.5x for tasks created this session, 1.0x default. (3) Session Retrospective comparing R(t) recommendations vs actual agent actions — guidance accuracy metric that self-calibrates routing weights. ARCHITECTURAL INSIGHT: This is the operating-systems working-set hypothesis applied to knowledge stores. The store is virtual memory. The session working set is the resident set. Guidance manages page faults (context switches to cold entities). TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-010 (R(t) routing), ADR-GUIDANCE-009, SEED.md §7 (Self-Improvement Loop), SEED.md §8 (Interface Principles)."
